passages.text: Gen- AI ramp up on rising client spending and AI total- solutions for comprehensive clients; Up to Buy with TP at HK\$2.72
0020.HK 12m Price Target: HK\$2.72 Price: HK\$2.09 Upside: \(30.0\%\)

The "AI Plus" guidelines were announced by the State Council in Aug 2025 (Link), highlighting AI monetization with ecosystem expansion, and we expect the rollout to encourage user spending on AI, driving Sensetime's generative AI business. 1H25 revenues were better- than- expected at \(36\%\) YoY, and management highlighted strong generative AI business growth at \(73\%\) YoY in 1H25, driven by productivity tools and interactive tools. With a supportive policy backdrop and Sensetime's comprehensive offerings (AI foundation model/ industry solution/ application software), we turn more positive on Sensetime's generative AI business, expecting the revenue contribution to increase from \(64\%\) in 2024 to \(91\%\) in 2030E. Along with market re- rating on China AI supply chain, we raise Sensetime's TP from HK\$1.83 to HK\$2.72. With \(30\%\) potential upside (vs. \(9\%\) average upside for our Greater China Technology coverage), we upgrade Sensetime to Buy from Neutral. Read more: Sensetime Initiation.

New state guidelines to encourage AI spending: The new guidelines by the State Council (Link) sets up a target of over \(70\%\) of new- generation intelligent terminals and AI agents penetration rate by 2027 in 6 key sectors (technology, industrial, consumer, welfare, governance, and global cooperation), highlighting actions plan to empower AI devices and improve efficiency. By 2030E, the new guidelines target AI penetration rate to achieve over \(90\%\) . Sensetime is transitioning to generative AI business, with \(77\%\) of revenue contributing from generative AI in 1H25 (vs. \(60\%\) in 1H24). With company's enhanced product matrix and demand from various industries, we expect Sensetime to accelerate generative AI development and, riding on the favorable policy backdrop.
1H25 revenue better- than- expected, GM in line: Company's 1H25 revenues is \(+36\%\) YoY, or \(6\%\) / \(9\%\) ahead of our/ Bloomberg

Expanding Gen- Al product offerings: Management notes the company plans to enhance the Al inferencing model (post the release of SenseNova v6.5), develop Al agents, and expand into Al robotics. We see the company has made progress on Al monetization, with Office Raccoon users having exceeded 3m in 1H25, and shipments of Al glasses empowered by Sensetime Al \(+280\%\) YoY. Moreover, Sensetime cooperated with local ecosystem partners to launch "SenseCore Mall" in Aug 2025, which incorporates the All- in- One Al machine, Al model APIs, and SuperPod for scale- up, offering one- stop model training/inferencing solution for clients (link). We also expect company's expansion to more comprehensive Gen- Al product offerings to drive new client penetration and rising spending on Gen- Al private cloud/Gen- Al projects.

Earnings revisions: We factor in 1H25 results, and revise our 2025/2026/27E to net losses of Rmb2.5bn/Rmb972m/Rmb238m (vs. previously at Rmb2.6bn/Rmb1,049m/Rmb250m) and revise up our 2028- 30E net income by \(5\% /7\% /6\%\) on higher revenues and higher GM. The revenues change are mainly on higher revenues of Gen- Al private cloud solution and Gen- Al project, reflecting our expectation for accelerated generative Al client penetration and rising client spending. GM is revised up by 0.1ppts- 0.5ppts in 2025- 30E due to product mix changes towards Gen- Al private cloud solution carrying higher margin than blended GM.

Valuation: Our valuation methodology remains unchanged. We derive our 12m target price of HK\$2.72 (vs. HK\$1.83) based on average of EV/ Sales valuation TP at HK\$2.84 and DCF valuation TP at HK\$2.6. Our target price implied EV/ Sales is at 14.5x (vs. previously at 9.6x), which is between company's avg. EV/Sales at 11x and avg. +1std EV/Sales at 16x since Jan 2023. With \(30\%\) implied upside (vs. \(9\%\) avg. upside for our coverage, as of Aug 28, 2025), we upgrade Sensetime from Neutral to Buy.

EV/Sales valuation: Our estimated 2026E EV/Sales value per share is HK\$2.84 (vs. HK\$2.03 previously) based on 15.2x 2026E EV/Sales (vs. previously at 10.7x). The 15.2x 2026E EV/Sales is derived from refreshed local and global peers EV/Sales vs. revenues YoY (methodology unchanged) based on company's higher revenues growth in 2026- 27E at \(31\%\) YoY (vs. previously at \(25\%\) YoY).

DCF valuation: Our DCF value per share is HK\$2.60 (vs. previously at HK\$1.64) based on higher FCF, WACC at \(10.7\%\) (vs. \(10.8\%\) previously due to updated equity to asset ratio at \(61\%\) ), and terminal growth rate at \(2\%\) (unchanged). We expect a higher FCF in 2026- 41E is driven by (1) higher NI with accelerated Gen- AI ramp up and mix upgrade, and (2) improving CCC days with larger revenues scale and growing focus on payment terms.

1. Slower-than-expected generative AI customers ramp up pace: We model generative AI as the key driver of the company's future growth. If the company sees a slower-than-expected generative customer ramp-up pace, it may create downside risk for the company.

2. Lower-than-expected customer spending: We model the company to have more customers that are willing to spend more for company's services annually. If customers' willingness to pay is lower than expected, it will decrease the company's revenue scale, and create downside risk.

3. Fiercer-than-expected market competition: The company faces competitions from other local AI application players. If market competition is fiercer than our expectation, the company may win fewer cases than expected, which will impact the revenue scale and create downside risk.

Valuation: We derive our 12m TP of HK\$2.72 based on the average of (1) our 2- stage DCF to capture the company's long- term growth opportunities (GenAI rising adoption across industries). We derive a DCF valuation of HK\$2.60 per share based on a WACC of \(10.7\%\) and a terminal growth rate of \(2\%\) . (2) target 2026E EV/Sales valuation to capture near- term momentum (e.g. GPU supply constraints, favorable local policy in AI deployment, etc.). Our target EV/Sales multiple of \(15.2x\) is derived from the correlation between EV/Sales and revenue growth of its peers, based on company's 2026- 27E revenue YoY growth of \(31\%\) , which gives a valuation of HK\$2.84.
Key risks: Slower- than- expected generative AI customers ramp up pace; Lower- than- expected customer spending; Fiercer- than- expected market competition.

Sensetime is a leading AI supplier in China, offering Gen- AI total solutions, from an AI foundation model (SenseNova) to customized industry models for AI application software (SenseAvatar/ SenseChat/ SenseMirage etc.), mainly targeting government and enterprise clients across varied industries. We see the company's offering of customized solutions with specific industry focus (Finance/TMT/Telecom etc.) supporting an accelerated ramp up.

With the emergence of DeepSeek AI model and reduced AI inferencing/training cost, we see more popular Gen- AI applications with a pathway to monetization across ToC, ToB and ToG clients. We are positive on the enhanced AI reasoning and multi- modal capabilities of SenseNova (v6.5), and its 5x higher inferencing efficiency to help reduce computing cost. We have a Buy rating on the stock.

The Goldman Sachs Factor Profile provides investment context for a stock by comparing key attributes to the market (i.e. our universe of rated stocks) and its sector peers. The four key attributes depicted are: Growth, Financial Returns, Multiple (e.g. valuation) and Integrated (a composite of Growth, Financial Returns and Multiple). Growth, Financial Returns and Multiple are calculated by using normalized ranks for specific metrics for each stock. The normalized ranks for the metrics are then averaged and converted into percentiles for the relevant attribute. The precise calculation of each metric may vary depending on the fiscal year, industry and region, but the standard approach is as follows:

Growth is based on a stock's forward- looking sales growth, EBITDA growth and EPS growth (for financial stocks, only EPS and sales growth), with a higher percentile indicating a higher growth company. Financial Returns is based on a stock's forward- looking ROE, ROCE and CROCI (for financial stocks, only ROE), with a higher percentile indicating a company with higher financial returns. Multiple is based on a stock's forward- looking P/E, P/B, price/dividend (P/D), EV/EBITDA, EV/FCF and EV/Debt Adjusted Cash Flow (DACF) (for financial stocks, only P/E, P/B and P/D), with a higher percentile indicating a stock trading at a higher multiple. The Integrated percentile is calculated as the average of the Growth percentile, Financial Returns percentile and (100% - Multiple percentile).

Financial Returns and Multiple use the Goldman Sachs analyst forecasts at the fiscal year- end at least three quarters in the future. Growth uses inputs for the fiscal year at least seven quarters in the future compared with the year at least three quarters in the future (on a per- share basis for all metrics).
For a more detailed description of how we calculate the GS Factor Profile, please contact your GS representative.

Across our global coverage, we examine stocks using an M&A framework, considering both qualitative factors and quantitative factors (which may vary across sectors and regions) to incorporate the potential that certain companies could be acquired. We then assign a M&A rank as a means of scoring companies under our rated coverage from 1 to 3, with 1 representing high (30%- 50%) probability of the company becoming an acquisition target, 2 representing medium (15%- 30%) probability and 3 representing low (0%- 15%) probability. For companies ranked 1 or 2, in line with our standard departmental guidelines we incorporate an M&A component into our target price. M&A rank of 3 is considered immaterial and therefore does not factor into our price target, and may or may not be discussed in research.
